race.comment: The in-form Seib barn has a strong hand. GHOST WALKER (1) is likely the best of them presenting off a narrow defeat in stronger at Rosehill. Has the inside barrier and is proven third-up. Winning rider Boudvillain is reunited. Stablemate ZIGGY ROSE (8) is lightly raced and delivered a Moruya Maiden stepping up to this journey. Started $2.0F and she looks capable of taking the next step. Draws inside and Guymer stays aboard. HURRICANE CONI (4) will present at peak for Joe Cleary and was quickly back on track when narrowly beaten here from the front over this trip. He can make the finish again. STAR EMPIRE (7) has been around the mark without winning and can't be ruled out with JVO riding first time.
